      <spirit:description>Each AHB-Lite slave has its own slave select signal HSELx and this signal indicates that the current transfer is intended for the selected slave. When the slave is initially selected, it must also monitor the status of HREADY to ensure that the previous bus transfer has completed,before it responds to the current transfer.
The HSELx signal is a combinatorial decode of the address bus.</spirit:description>
